    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="1218"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1218">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/34815</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Apostolic Delegate at Washington</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cicognani</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-22">June 22,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Archbishop</hi>: I refer to your memorandum of June
                    12 and your letter of June 17, 1944,<note n="52" xml:id="d1218fn1">Letter not
                        printed.</note> in which, in connection with the military operations of the
                    Allied forces in Italy, you express the concern of the Holy See for the safety
                    of the Italian capital and request that this matter be brought to the attention
                    of the competent authorities with a view to ensuring the protecion of Rome.</p>
                <p>I am glad to inform you that your communications, which have received the
                    Department’s most careful attention, have been duly transmitted to the competent
                    authorities for their consideration and such action as may be deemed
                    appropriate.</p>
                <p>I shall communicate with you again on this subject at the earliest possible
                    date.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cordell Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
